showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:1}); // Chole

“Ever since Mom and Dad died,

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:4}); // Chole
“Welcome!

you scratch behind its ears.”{PAUSE}“But if you scratch it someplace that

so be careful.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:106}); // Chole
“Hey, do you know what
a Chocobo Sage is?”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:107}); // Chole
“What!?
You've actually met him!?”{PAUSE}“Wow!
What did he tell you?”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:108}); // Chole
“Wow, that's amazing!
…Let me take some notes.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:119}); // Chole
“There are no Chocobos.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:120}); // Chole
“Hey, there's only one Chocobo.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:112}); // Chole
“For telling me that story,
I'll tell you about each
Chocobo's abilities.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:115}); // Chole
“From what I see,
the fastest sprinter is…”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:116}); // Chole
“And, the fastest one is…”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:117}); // Chole
“Also, from what I can tell,
the one with the most stamina is…”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:118}); // Chole
“Finally,
the most intelligent one is…”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:121}); // Other than regular Chocobo, there are
'Mountain Chocobo' and 'River-Chocobo'.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:122}); // In order for the 'Mountain Chocobo' and
'River Chocobo' to be born,{PAUSE}Feed the 'Carob Nut' to
a 'Great Chocobo'
or a 'Good Chocobo' and
have it produce an egg.{PAUSE}But we don't sell any
'Carob Nuts'.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:123}); // A 'Great Chocobo' and
a 'Good Chocobo' are found…{PAUSE}on an island southeast
of the Chocobo Sage's dwelling at Corel
and in the area west of Corel.{PAUSE}The 'Carob Nut' can be
found south of the Chocobo Sage's dwelling.
Monsters carry them.{PAUSE}Let's see, is Bone Village
just south of there?

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:124}); // One surprise:
If you get the “Mountain Chocobo“ and
the “River Chocobo“ to produce an egg,{PAUSE}You'll get a Chocobo that
can cross mountains and rivers.
I bet that the right nut for
that is the “Carob Nut.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:125}); // Bigger surprise:
There seems to be a Chocobo
that can cross the ocean.{PAUSE}If you could cross the ocean,
mountains, and rivers,
there'd be no place you couldn't go.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:126}); // In order to get an Ocean Chocobo
you need to get a Mountain-and-River Chocobo
to mate with something else.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:127}); // If you mate the Mountain-and-River Chocobo
with a 'Wonderful Chocobo',{PAUSE}you'll get an Ocean Chocobo.
But to do that you can't
use an ordinary Nut.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:128}); // The 'Nut' that produces
Ocean Chocobos is the 'Zeio Nut'.{PAUSE}This is the first I've ever heard of it.
I wonder where you get them?

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:129}); // Zeio Nuts are found on a little island
east of the Chocobo Sage.{PAUSE}'Goblins' have them.
With this, you can produce
an 'Ocean Chocobo'.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:130}); // According to my research,
Mountain, River, and Ocean Chocobos
are hard to produce.{PAUSE}But, if you take the right care
of the Chocobo and increase their
Class ranking by winning at the races,
it'll increase your chances of getting one.

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:109}); // Chole
“Hey, did you ever see
the Chocobo Sage again?
What did he tell you?”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:108}); // Chole
“Wow, that's amazing!
…Let me take some notes.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:4}); // Chole
“Welcome!
Here's some good advice.”{PAUSE}“The white Chocobo likes it when
you scratch behind its ears.”{PAUSE}“But if you scratch it someplace that
it doesn't like, it'll get mad,
so be careful.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:8}); // Choco Billy
“Do you want a Chocobo?”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:10}); // Choco Billy
“You old folks are out of luck!”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:13}); // Choco Billy
“We're all out of Chocobos.
I'm taking care of the ones
out there for someone else.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:12}); // Choco Billy
“Oh, I'm so glad!”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:14}); // Choco Billy
“You know, if you really want a Chocobo,
you should go out and catch one.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:16}); // Choco Billy
“You see those claw prints out there?
Wild Chocobo's will appear
in those areas.”{PAUSE}“But, if you don't have 'Chocobo Lure'
they won't come out.
They're very cautious by nature.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:18}); // Choco Billy
“'Chocobo Lure' is a type
of Materia which
attracts Chocobos.”{PAUSE}“If you equip this,
they'll come to you.
But, without it,
they won't appear.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:19}); // Choco Billy
“A wild Chocobo always
appears with other monsters.”{PAUSE}“But, you won't be able to catch it
because of the monsters.”{PAUSE}“That is why you must defeat
the monsters first
before you catch the Chocobo.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:21}); // Choco Billy
“Wild Chocobos are really cautious.
They'll run away from the smallest things.”{PAUSE}“But, if you use 'Greens'
they'll focus on them
and won't run away.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:22}); // Choco Billy
“Whatever you do, don't make Chocobos angry.
They're usually calm, but if you get
them angry, you'll get hurt.”{PAUSE}“Oh, and remember,
once you get off a Chocobo,
it'll escape.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:23}); // Choco Billy
“Well then, shall we get down to business?”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:24}); // Choco Billy
“I'll sell you the 'Chocobo Lure' for
2000 gil, right now.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:27}); // Choco Billy
“Hey, you don't have enough.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:30}); // Choco Billy
“It wouldn't hurt to
buy some 'Greens', either.”{PAUSE}“Oh, and how fast a Chocobo'll
finish eating depends on
what type of 'Greens' you feed them.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:28}); // Choco Billy
“Mmmm, if you don't have it,
you'll never catch one.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:27}); // Choco Billy
“Hey, you don't have enough.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:30}); // Choco Billy
“It wouldn't hurt to
buy some 'Greens', either.”{PAUSE}“Oh, and how fast a Chocobo'll

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:28}); // Choco Billy
“Mmmm, if you don't have it,
you'll never catch one.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:59}); // Choco Billy
“What the Chocobo eats are 'Greens'.
The most famous one is
the 'Gysahl Greens'.”{PAUSE}“Chocobos will mature differently
depending on which 'Greens'
they eat. Certain 'Greens' will
boost their stamina.”{PAUSE}“You'll have to figure out which kinds
have what effects for yourselves.”{PAUSE}“Oh, and Chocobos are born with certain
natural abilities. So, no matter
how much they mature, they can't get
more abilities than what they're born with.”{PAUSE}“If a Chocobo's abilities don't
increase even when you feed it,
that means it's reached its limit.”{PAUSE}“It's best to let those kinds of
Chocobo go or mate them to
get a new Chocobo.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:60}); // Choco Billy
“A male and a female Chocobo together can
produce an egg.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:58}); // Choco Billy
“Yeah, you can ride this one.”{PAUSE}“And even if you take it outside,
this Chocobo won't run away
when you get off of it.”{PAUSE}“If you want to return it to
your 'Chocobo Stable',
just ride it onto the farm.”{PAUSE}“Then, you'll be able to
feed it again.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:61}); // Choco Billy
“The Chocobo out there is part of the
stock that you caught.”{PAUSE}“We can only keep 4 Chocobos here at once.
If you get a fifth one,
the first one will have to be let go.”{PAUSE}“If you don't want that to happen,
come back and put it in your own stable.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:62}); // Choco Billy
“Chocobos' strengths are
divided by 'Class'.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:39}); // Choco Billy
“You don't even have
any 'Chocobo Stables'”{PAUSE}“If you want to raise Chocobos,
go talk to Grandpa.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:38}); // Choco Billy
“You have all the 'Chocobo Stables'
you can carry.”{PAUSE}“If you want to put a Chocobo in it,
first, you must let it go
and open a 'Chocobo Stable.'”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:40}); // Choco Billy
“It looks like you haven't
even caught one yet…”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:41}); // Choco Billy
“Which one are you going to put in
the 'Chocobo Stable'?”{PAUSE}“Use the Directional button
left or right and {PURPLE}[OK]{WHITE}.”
